<bibRefCitation author="Bohlmann, F" journalOrPublisher="Plant Systematics and Evolution" pageId="50" pageNumber="99" pagination="3 - 43" publicationUrl="10.1007/978-3-7091-6928-5_2" refId="B5" refString="Bohlmann, F, Jakupovic, J, 1990. Progress in the chemistry of the Vernonieae (Compositae). Plant Systematics and Evolution 4: 3 - 43, DOI: 10.1007/978-3-7091-6928-5_2" title="Progress in the chemistry of the Vernonieae (Compositae)." url="10.1007/978-3-7091-6928-5_2" volume="4" year="1990">Bohlmann and Jakupovic 1990</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Compositae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vernonia galpinii" order="Asterales" pageId="42" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="galpinii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="91">Vernonia galpinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Klatt).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="42" pageNumber="91">
The genus consists of mostly monocephalous species, but those species have many individual differences such as the restriction of leaves to a basal rosette, capitula structure, and pubescence of the achenes. They do have essentially identical pollen, but it is a widely distributed pollen type in the 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="42" pageNumber="91" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Erlangeinae" subtribe="Erlangeinae">Erlangeinae</taxonomicName>
. There are no unique or uncommon characteristics that the two species share.
</paragraph>
